<h2>Preparation of a paper in English</h2>

<p>A paper submission MUST include:
<ul>
  <li>File of the paper in <a href="http://www.miktex.org">MikTex 2.9+ (LaTeX)</a> 
		or <a href="http://www.microsoft.com/office">Microsoft Word</a> formats</li>
  <ul>
      <li>prepared in accordance with <strong>Journal <a href="#template-files">templates</a></strong>:</li>
      <li>Title of the paper</li>
      <li>Authors' surnames</li>
      <li>affiliation</li>
      <li>e-mail address</li>
      <li>abstract</li>
      <li>keywords</li>
      <li>text of the paper</li>
  </ul>
  <li>PDF-file of the paper</li>
    <li>Text file in Plain Text (<a href="$ResourceLink$/info-eng.txt">info-eng.txt</a>) containing:</li>
  <ul>
      <li>paper title</li>
      <li>surname, first name, patronymic</li>
      <li>affiliation (work place, institution, address, position)</li>
      <li>academic status and degree</li>
      <li>e-mail</li>
      <li>abstract</li>      
      <li>keywords</li>
      <li>full reference to the paper (without page numbers)</li>
  </ul>
  <li>The file containing references in HTML or Microsoft Word format</li>
</ul>
</p>

<p>The abstract is an independent part of the paper relating the most important ideas and results of the research. It should be a short description of the paper and has to contain the problem statement, the author's approach and principal results.
</p>
<p><strong>The abstract should not contain formulas.</strong></p>
<p>
The introduction provides background information and serves as a guide to the 
author's approach. The introduction does not present a replication 
of the abstract.
</p>

<p>
The paper is prepared in accordance with the journal style. 
</p><p>
<strong>Submissions not prepared according to the rules are not considered.</strong>
</p><p>
The paper size is not limited.
</p>

