<h2>Preparation of the article in TEX-format</h2>
<a name="template-files"> </a>
<p>You should use <a href="http://www.miktex.org">MikTex 2.9+</a> with journal templates</p>
<p>How to apply the templates for MikTex:
 <ul>
   <li>Download file <a href="$ResourceLink$/auth-for-tex.zip">author-for-tex.zip</a> from the journal site to your computer and unpack it</li>
   <li>Select the folder <em>eng</em> </li>
   <li>Open file <em>english.tex</em> and follow instructions from comments in the file (write your paper title, authors, and the first page number)</li>
   <li>Open file <em>diff_eng.sty</em> and write the journal number and the year of publishing</li>
   <li>Open file <em>diff_eng.tex</em> and write the journal number, the year of publishing and the field of study that the paper relates</li>
   <li>Check that your article is compiled by the command "<em>pdflatex english.tex</em>" in MikTex 2.9+</li>
 </ul>
</p>

<p>Pay your attention that abstract and keywords have the same font size as main text - 12pt. Abstract has the format \noindent{\bf Abstract.} text of abstract. Then  \noindent {\bf  Keywords:} keywords follow.<br>
    Do not use environments   Title, Author.
</p>

<p>Information about last versions of TEX you can find on the site <a href="http://www.miktex.org">http://www.miktex.org</a>.
LaTeX is a module in the MikTEX package</p>

<h2>Preparation of the article in Microsoft Word</h2>
<p>Paper should be prepared in version MSWORD 2007 (or higher) with using formula editor.</p>

<p>
 <ul>
    <li>Download file <a href="$ResourceLink$/auth-for-doc.zip">author-for-doc.zip</a> from the journal site and unpack it.</li>
    <li>Select file <em>template-eng.docx</em> and open it in Microsoft Word</li>
    <li>Insert the text of your article into the template file in accordance with template styles.</li>
    <li>Save the document as  <em>YOUR_NAME.docx</em>.</li>
 </ul>
</p>

